(*): Load values for 0.6 bar are for calculating dual and triple load values only.



30 km/h (up to 40 km/h) load values also apply for low-speed high-torque field work.



For plowing with single driven tyres in the furrow, a minimum inflation pressure of 0.8 bar is required.



For intensive road transport at 90/65/50/40/30 km/h the pressure must be increased by 0.4 bar. Maximum inflation pressure should never be exceeded.



All load values are valid for ground slopes up to and including 20% (11). When operating on slopes greater than 20%, please, contact the producer.
